{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-91d63ff797978938", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# MambaVoiceCloning: Efficient and Expressive Text-to-Speech via State-Space Modeling and Diffusion Control\narXiv: 2604.00292\nAuthors: Sahil Kumar, Namrataben Patel, Honggang Wang, Youshan Zhang\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A diffusion-based TTS system with a fully SSM-only inference-time conditioning path spanning text, rhythm, and prosody under a fixed decoder.\n  2. A gated bidirectional Mamba fusion with AdaLN that improves long-range prosody stability and reduces drift on multi-sentence and out-of-distribution text.\n  3. Protocol- and capacity-matched baselines that isolate the architectural impact of removing inference-time attention.\n  4. A deployment-oriented analysis covering memory usage, throughput, SSM hyperparameter sensitivity, long-form behavior, and finite look-ahead streaming, demonstrating predictable linear-time characteristics.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-流式\n===\n# SpeechLLM-as-Judges: Towards General and Interpretable Speech Quality Evaluation\narXiv: 2510.14664\nAuthors: Hui Wang, Jinghua Zhao, Yifan Yang, Shujie Liu, Junyang Chen, Yanzhe Zhang, Shiwan Zhao, Jinyu Li, Jiaming Zhou, Haoqin Sun, Yan Lu, Yong Qin\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present SpeechEval, a large-scale dataset for speech quality evaluation, containing 128,754 annotations across languages, domains, and evaluation types.\n  2. We propose SQ-LLM, a speech-quality-aware model trained in two stages: instruction tuning with chain-of-thought reasoning and reward learning via GRPO.\n  3. We conduct extensive experiments to evaluate the effectiveness of the SpeechLLM-as-Judges paradigm, demonstrating its advantages in accuracy, interpretability, and generalization across tasks and domains.\n\nTags: Eval, Eval/LLM, LALM, LALM/后训练-GRPO", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "3becb783-1d57-4f2f-807d-c781f6aeba7b", "uuid": "6b3c9c0c-301d-4c65-bfb7-abc2f1c23e70", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T05:20:47.193Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# MambaVoiceCloning: Efficient and Expressive Text-to-Speech via State-Space Modeling and Diffusion Control\narXiv: 2604.00292\nAuthors: Sahil Kumar, Namrataben Patel, Honggang Wang, Youshan Zhang\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A diffusion-based TTS system with a fully SSM-only inference-time conditioning path spanning text, rhythm, and prosody under a fixed decoder.\n  2. A gated bidirectional Mamba fusion with AdaLN that improves long-range prosody stability and reduces drift on multi-sentence and out-of-distribution text.\n  3. Protocol- and capacity-matched baselines that isolate the architectural impact of removing inference-time attention.\n  4. A deployment-oriented analysis covering memory usage, throughput, SSM hyperparameter sensitivity, long-form behavior, and finite look-ahead streaming, demonstrating predictable linear-time characteristics.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-流式\n===\n# SpeechLLM-as-Judges: Towards General and Interpretable Speech Quality Evaluation\narXiv: 2510.14664\nAuthors: Hui Wang, Jinghua Zhao, Yifan Yang, Shujie Liu, Junyang Chen, Yanzhe Zhang, Shiwan Zhao, Jinyu Li, Jiaming Zhou, Haoqin Sun, Yan Lu, Yong Qin\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present SpeechEval, a large-scale dataset for speech quality evaluation, containing 128,754 annotations across languages, domains, and evaluation types.\n  2. We propose SQ-LLM, a speech-quality-aware model trained in two stages: instruction tuning with chain-of-thought reasoning and reward learning via GRPO.\n  3. We conduct extensive experiments to evaluate the effectiveness of the SpeechLLM-as-Judges paradigm, demonstrating its advantages in accuracy, interpretability, and generalization across tasks and domains.\n\nTags: Eval, Eval/LLM, LALM, LALM/后训练-GRPO", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
